articles.description: Check out the best of the best from Week 13 in the NFL.
articles.headline: Week 13 NFL highlights: Best plays, moments, touchdowns

images.name: Aaron Rodgers [600x400]
images.caption: Aaron Rodgers completed just 10 of 21 attempts for 117 yards in Sunday's loss, marking his third-lowest total in any game where he threw at least 20 passes.

articles.description: After an injured Aaron Rodgers finished one of the worst passing games of his career, the Steelers QB said he hopes his wide receivers show up during the next film sessions and run the right routes.
articles.headline: Aaron Rodgers calls out WRs, says Steelers earned fans' boos

images.name: Justin Herbert not concerned about hand injury
images.caption: Justin Herbert speaks to reporters about his lack of concern over his hand injury, which could cause him to miss games.

articles.description: Justin Herbert speaks to reporters about his lack of concern over his hand injury, which could cause him to miss games.
articles.headline: Justin Herbert not concerned about hand injury

images.name: Lane Kiffin [1296x729]
images.alt: Ole Miss Rebels coach Lane Kiffin argues a call during the college football game between the Ole Miss Rebels and the Mississippi State Bulldogs on November 28, 2025, at Davis Wade Stadium in Starkville, MS.
images.caption: Lane Kiffin's decision about where he'll coach in 2026 triggered a guessing game at sportsbooks over the weekend.

articles.description: How sportsbooks are evaluating Ole Miss and the College Football Playoff race, and more on NFL underdogs winning big on Thanksgiving.
articles.headline: Inside the 'guessing' game of Kiffin's decision, plus a dominant Thanksgiving for NFL underdogs

articles.description: Vikings quarterback J.J. McCarthy could be cleared from the concussion protocol as soon as Monday, coach Kevin O'Connell said Sunday, and be in line to start Minnesota's Week 14 game against Washington.
articles.headline: Vikings hopeful J.J. McCarthy clears protocol, starts Week 14

articles.description: Titans running back Julius Chestnut alleged that Jaguars punter Logan Cooke threatened to kill him during Sunday's game. "I was just trying to play hard, and he came up to me and said he was going to kill me," Chestnut said.
articles.headline: Titans' Chestnut alleges Jaguars' Cooke threatened him
